name: FInterpCurvePointFloat
doc:
Describes one specific point on an interpolation curve.
@note This is a mirror of TInterpCurvePoint<float>, defined in InterpCurvePoint.h

InVal: Float input value that corresponds to this key (eg. time).
OutVal: Float output value type when input is equal to InVal.
ArriveTangent: Tangent of curve arriving at this point.
LeaveTangent: Tangent of curve leaving this point.
InterpMode: Interpolation mode between this point and the next one.
